---
import ContactCTA from '../components/ContactCTA.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="The Agentic CMO — A Playbook for the Hybrid Marketing Team"
	description="The definitive guide to building hybrid intelligence marketing organisations. By Francesco Federico, Global CMO at S&P Global."
	image="/assets/book-cover.png"
>
	<script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
		{
			"@context": "https://schema.org",
			"@type": "Book",
			"name": "The Agentic CMO",
			"author": {
				"@type": "Person",
				"name": "Francesco Federico"
			},
			"description": "A playbook for the hybrid marketing team",
			"url": "https://amzn.eu/d/5kVB51B",
			"image": "https://francescofederico.com/assets/book-cover.png"
		}
	</script>
	<div class="stack gap-20">
		<main class="wrapper book stack gap-12">
			<Hero title="The Agentic CMO" tagline="A playbook for the hybrid marketing team" align="start">
				<img src="/assets/book-cover.png" alt="The Agentic CMO book cover" width="420" height="620" />
			</Hero>

			<section class="content stack gap-4">
				<p>
					Most organisations still treat AI as a productivity layer. That framing is already outdated.
				</p>
				<p>
					In <em>The Agentic CMO</em>, I lay out what senior marketing leaders need next: a practical operating model for hybrid intelligence, where human judgement and agentic execution are designed to work together. I break down bounded autonomy frameworks, governance patterns that protect brand and compliance, and measurement systems that track business value instead of vanity metrics.
				</p>
				<p>
					I wrote this from operating experience at S&amp;P Global and JLL, where pilot programmes only mattered if they survived scale. The book is built as a pilot-to-scale playbook: where to start, what to sequence, how to redesign talent, and which decisions a CMO must keep central as autonomy increases. No hype — only what stands up under board-level scrutiny.
				</p>
				<a class="button" href="https://amzn.eu/d/5kVB51B" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Buy on Amazon</a>
			</section>

			<section class="author stack gap-3">
				<h2>About the Author</h2>
				<p>
					Francesco Federico is Chief Marketing Officer at S&amp;P Global, author of <em>The Agentic CMO</em>, and publisher of <em>Chronicles of Change</em>. He advises executive teams on hybrid intelligence strategy, organisational design, and enterprise marketing transformation.
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>
		<ContactCTA />
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.book img {
		border-radius: 1rem;
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
	}

	.content {
		max-width: 75ch;
	}

	.button {
		display: inline-block;
		width: fit-content;
		padding: 0.9rem 1.4rem;
		border-radius: 0.75rem;
		text-decoration: none;
		background: var(--accent-regular);
		color: var(--accent-text-over);
		font-weight: 700;
	}
</style>
